According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) Services market was valued at USD 1.01 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 1.48 billion in 2026 to USD 17.02 billion by 2034, registering an impressive CAGR of 45.5% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing extraordinary growth as businesses increasingly shift from traditional Search Engine Optimization (SEO) toward optimizing digital content for AI-powered search experiences. GEO services enable organizations to improve their visibility within AI-generated answers, conversational search interfaces, and generative search platforms by developing structured, authoritative, verifiable, and context-rich content that artificial intelligence models can accurately interpret, cite, and recommend.
